{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01U69CLtduJZkAzL4Fn2myYF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"After 120 seconds (24 attempts x 5 seconds), the secret hasn't propagated. This is unusual. Let me check the kubelet's configuration for the secret sync frequency.\n\nWait, this might be because the StatefulSet uses `subPath` mounts for the volume files. When you mount a volume with `subPath`, the files are **not** updated when the secret changes! This is a known Kubernetes limitation.\n\nFrom the StatefulSet YAML:\n```yaml\n- name: file-realm\n  mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users\n  subPath: users\n  readOnly: true\n- name: file-realm\n  mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users_roles\n  subPath: users_roles\n  readOnly: true\n- name: file-realm\n  mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/roles.yml\n  subPath: roles.yml\n  readOnly: true\n```\n\nAll three mounts use `subPath`, which means they won't auto-update when the secret changes. I need to do a rolling restart of the StatefulSet to pick up the new secret values.\n\nI'll trigger a rolling restart using `kubectl rollout restart` on the StatefulSet. The rolling update strategy will restart pods one at a time based on the `updateStrategy` settings, and with a 3-node cluster, the cluster should maintain health throughout the restart process.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":467,"cache_read_input_tokens":48570,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":467},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bbd6817d-c71d-4eff-ad40-1d448284c028","uuid":"b0863987-d63a-473a-a1da-be66c57047cc","request_id":"req_011CcRDtwVZJLE4WEF1FcggB"}
