{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MDwEJzn7iPY3R9tRLZjgij","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle passes. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Root cause:** The `report-user` existed only in the `user-provided-file-realm` secret, but Elasticsearch's StatefulSet was configured to load the file realm exclusively from `es-file-realm-aggregate` (mounted via the `file-realm` volume). The aggregate only contained `ops-user`.\n\n**Fix:**\n1. Merged `report-user`'s `users` and `users_roles` entries from `user-provided-file-realm` into `es-file-realm-aggregate`.\n2. Triggered a rolling restart of the `es-cluster` StatefulSet — necessary because the volume files were mounted with `subPath`, which prevents Kubernetes from auto-updating them when the secret changes.\n\n**Result:** All 3 nodes restarted cleanly (cluster remained green throughout), both `ops-user` and `report-user` are now in the file realm, and `report-user` can read the `app-data` index with the `viewer` role."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":175,"cache_read_input_tokens":54850,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":175},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bbd6817d-c71d-4eff-ad40-1d448284c028","uuid":"22163762-04bf-45f7-a15f-2062c9c915b2","request_id":"req_011CcREWcX3oJNmRpYT4LxBg"}
